01:32.080 --> 01:34.036
♪ Hallelujah

01:45.640 --> 01:47.596
(Baby crying)

02:01.400 --> 02:03.311
He's asleep.

02:03.400 --> 02:05.356
Good job.

02:06.800 --> 02:08.756
(Crying starts again)

02:11.400 --> 02:13.311
My turn.

02:13.400 --> 02:15.356
You go back to sleep.

02:20.400 --> 02:22.356
What do you mean, back?

02:28.800 --> 02:30.756
(Alarm bleeps)

02:37.080 --> 02:40.868
Oye, hay este chico, que no se
como se llama pero...ay, qué mono!

02:40.960 --> 02:42.871
Tienes hombre ahora?

02:42.960 --> 02:44.871
No? Por qué?

02:44.960 --> 02:48.873
♪ What a beautiful morning
What a wonderful day

02:49.920 --> 02:52.992
♪ l gotta a beautiful feeling l'm ready...

02:55.640 --> 02:57.551
You're in a good mood.

02:57.640 --> 03:00.996
Why not? The sun is shining,
the pound is up against the dollar,

03:01.080 --> 03:03.514
and the memory of last night still lingers.

03:03.600 --> 03:06.319
Now you're off the pill,
don't you think it's better?

03:06.400 --> 03:08.595
lt's certainly more frequent.

03:14.320 --> 03:18.108
Hey, let me know when you'll be
home and l'll run us a bath.

03:18.200 --> 03:19.315
What?

03:19.400 --> 03:22.437
After we've got clean, we can get filthy.

03:22.520 --> 03:24.795
l'm sorry. l've got to go.

03:24.880 --> 03:26.836
..Pasa por aquí con nosotros?

03:26.920 --> 03:30.230
Why is Ramona always speaking
Spanish on the phone?

03:30.320 --> 03:32.276
Me voy. Adiós.

03:34.000 --> 03:35.956
Here, Josh. You hungry?

03:47.400 --> 03:49.356
Navigation Road.

03:55.200 --> 03:59.318
♪ Only love

04:00.120 --> 04:02.076
So, where are you living at the moment?

04:02.160 --> 04:04.913
Opposite sides of town.
We're after somewhere together.

04:05.000 --> 04:06.831
Well, you're wise to rent, not buy.

04:06.920 --> 04:09.434
Really? You think it makes financial sense?

04:09.520 --> 04:13.035
Good God, no,
it's much simpler when you split up.

04:18.399 --> 04:22.029
And by process of elimination,
this must be the lounge.

04:22.120 --> 04:24.270
Which way does the garden face?

04:24.360 --> 04:26.351
That way. Er...south, l think.

04:26.440 --> 04:28.715
Not that it makes any difference
in Manchester.

04:28.800 --> 04:30.711
Oh, Adam, it's perfect.

04:30.800 --> 04:33.837
- Of course, it's also expensive.
- Hey, we can afford it!

04:33.920 --> 04:38.675
Think of all the savings we'll make living
together - heating, food, toilet paper.

04:38.760 --> 04:41.035
lt's got a second bedroom.
That could be handy.

04:41.120 --> 04:43.315
Yes, you might want one each one day.

04:44.360 --> 04:46.316
Oh, it is nice.

04:47.360 --> 04:49.715
l can really see us living here...

04:50.160 --> 04:52.230
lf yet l have not all thy love,

04:52.320 --> 04:55.517
Dear, l shall never have it all

04:55.600 --> 04:58.353
<i>I cannot breathe one other sigh to move</i>

04:58.440 --> 05:01.512
Nor can entreat one other tear to fall...

05:04.040 --> 05:05.951
So can l.

05:21.200 --> 05:23.430
- Let's take it.
- Sure it's not too expensive?

05:23.520 --> 05:25.431
We can manage, and if not...

05:25.520 --> 05:27.476
l'll forget the pool table.

05:29.200 --> 05:31.156
What pool table?

05:34.200 --> 05:36.270
l don't know. Do we really want to go skiing?

05:36.360 --> 05:38.271
We go every year.

05:38.360 --> 05:40.954
Precisely. Let's do something else for a change.

05:41.040 --> 05:43.110
OK. What about the Caribbean?

05:43.200 --> 05:45.111
Or the Lake District.

05:45.200 --> 05:47.111
The Lake District?

05:47.200 --> 05:50.158
No flight delays.
You get some very good deals in the winter.

05:50.240 --> 05:53.516
Yeah, because it's winter. No-one wants to go.

05:53.600 --> 05:55.909
Well, maybe we should wait till August.

05:56.000 --> 05:57.718
Are we suddenly poor or something?

05:57.800 --> 06:00.155
No! No, we're not poor.

06:01.800 --> 06:04.758
We're just a bit...strapped.

06:14.200 --> 06:18.478
You know how they say that investments...
can go down as well as up?

06:18.560 --> 06:20.471
Yes?

06:20.560 --> 06:22.516
Well, ours have...

06:27.760 --> 06:30.035
lt was this chap l know in the City.

06:30.120 --> 06:33.954
He asked me if l wanted to invest
in a new golf course...

06:35.000 --> 06:36.956
..in Africa.

06:38.680 --> 06:41.638
Well, there are very few golf courses in Africa.

06:41.720 --> 06:43.676
There are very few golfers.

06:43.760 --> 06:45.716
There's a rising urban elite.

06:46.640 --> 06:48.596
At least there was, until the coup.

06:48.680 --> 06:50.750
How much have we lost?

06:50.840 --> 06:53.638
- Si quieres venir el martes...
- She's at it again.

06:54.520 --> 06:56.988
There can't be that many Spaniards
in Britain!

06:58.080 --> 07:01.072
She's on the phone to her mother.
lt's her 60th birthday.

07:01.160 --> 07:04.072
- What's wrong with a card?
- How much, David?

07:07.240 --> 07:09.196
£1 5,000.

07:11.240 --> 07:17.156
You put £1 5,000 of our money
into some harebrained scheme?

07:17.240 --> 07:18.958
lt was not harebrained.

07:19.040 --> 07:20.758
lt looked like a sure thing.

07:20.840 --> 07:22.831
Oh, right. Lovely, darling.

07:22.920 --> 07:26.117
What other 'sure things'
are we investing in?

07:26.200 --> 07:29.317
An off-licence in Saudi,
a nightclub in lran?

07:29.400 --> 07:31.436
Euro-bloody-tunnel?

07:31.520 --> 07:33.476
We do have some Eurotunnel shares, yeah.

07:35.120 --> 07:37.156
David, why didn't you tell me?

07:37.240 --> 07:39.231
Well, you weren't interested in the past.

07:39.320 --> 07:41.276
Well, rest assured, l am now.

07:42.120 --> 07:44.680
l suggest you get on the phone
to our accountant.

07:44.760 --> 07:47.558
lt's time we reassessed our portfolio.

07:50.280 --> 07:52.191
Jen?

07:52.280 --> 07:54.236
No!

08:02.240 --> 08:04.196
Right, wipes.

08:04.280 --> 08:06.236
Oh, yeah.

08:11.160 --> 08:13.116
One of them.

08:18.640 --> 08:20.551
What's that for?

08:20.640 --> 08:22.596
l don't know!

08:23.640 --> 08:26.916
How did our parents cope without all this help?

08:27.000 --> 08:29.958
Right. Baby alarms...

08:33.000 --> 08:34.717
This one'll do.

08:34.799 --> 08:36.232
No, this one's better.

08:37.080 --> 08:38.832
Yeah, and it's 30 quid more.

08:38.919 --> 08:43.357
You get what you pay for.
Anyway, this one's 'stylishly designed'.

08:44.120 --> 08:47.669
- And you can use it abroad.
- Oh, that is an impressive range.

08:48.440 --> 08:51.398
Pete! lt is recommended by What Baby?

08:51.480 --> 08:53.835
And it's 30 quid more.

08:53.920 --> 08:56.514
Do you want the best for our child or not?

09:02.240 --> 09:05.550
l had to go to Safeway's.
We've had all the Tesco's boxes.

09:05.640 --> 09:08.074
Remember those two waiters in Berlin?

09:09.160 --> 09:11.116
Oh, my God! Rolf and Ralf!

09:12.160 --> 09:14.071
Which one did you shag?

09:14.160 --> 09:15.559
Neither.

09:15.640 --> 09:17.153
l shagged them both.

09:17.240 --> 09:19.151
You did not?

09:19.240 --> 09:21.151
You foul slut!

09:21.240 --> 09:22.275
No way!

09:22.360 --> 09:24.112
(Phone rings)

09:26.000 --> 09:26.955
Hello?

09:27.040 --> 09:29.270
<i>Hi, gorgeous, how's it going?</i>

09:29.360 --> 09:32.033
Erm, OK.
l'd say we were getting there.

09:32.120 --> 09:33.997
You are brutally throwing stuff out?

09:34.080 --> 09:36.514
<i>Yeah, there's an Oxfam piIe right here.</i>

09:36.600 --> 09:41.469
Presuming they want a 20-year-old Blue Peter
annual and a small plastic gnome.

09:41.560 --> 09:42.834
l gave you the gnome!

09:43.560 --> 09:46.472
<i>And keep the BIue Peter annuaI,
it might be worth something.</i>

09:46.560 --> 09:49.358
l'm almost done here. l'll see you at the house.

09:49.440 --> 09:51.590
<i>Would that be our house?</i>

09:51.680 --> 09:53.591
ln the middle of our street.

09:53.680 --> 09:55.636
See you.

09:56.680 --> 09:58.636
Love that girl.

10:05.640 --> 10:07.835
Which one of us do you think he takes after?

10:07.920 --> 10:09.433
(Passes wind)

10:09.520 --> 10:11.829
Clever boy! You.

10:11.920 --> 10:13.831
Will you change him?

10:13.920 --> 10:15.831
Do you know, l wish we could.

10:15.920 --> 10:17.353
Only joking.

10:17.440 --> 10:19.715
l've just got back from work. l'm a bit knackered.

10:19.800 --> 10:21.711
So am l.

10:21.800 --> 10:23.950
l've still got to get the tea on.

10:24.040 --> 10:25.996
Right, there you go.

10:27.040 --> 10:29.952
Careful, it's a follow-through.

10:31.040 --> 10:32.951
Ooh, you little monkey.

10:33.040 --> 10:34.996
Come here.

10:51.840 --> 10:53.193
Blimey.

10:53.280 --> 10:55.316
Never mind. We'll clean you up. Come here.

10:55.400 --> 10:56.628
That's it.

10:59.440 --> 11:01.351
There we go.

11:01.440 --> 11:03.396
Hey! O-oh, tots.

11:05.280 --> 11:07.271
lt's only wee. lt's only wee.

11:10.040 --> 11:11.951
Right, come here.

11:12.040 --> 11:14.270
Right, up we go.

11:15.360 --> 11:17.316
(Ploop)

11:20.440 --> 11:22.396
Jenny!

11:23.880 --> 11:25.359
(Turns volume up)

11:25.440 --> 11:27.112
Jenny!

11:36.120 --> 11:38.270
(Car radio plays) ♪ MADNESS: Our House

11:42.600 --> 11:45.160
- lt looks like they're moving in next door.
- Really?

11:45.240 --> 11:48.152
This is yours?
l thought you were throwing stuff out!

11:48.240 --> 11:50.151
l was. l told you.

11:50.240 --> 11:52.310
Yeah, a plant pot and an old Blue Peter annual.

11:52.400 --> 11:54.311
No, l kept the annual.

11:54.400 --> 11:56.311
You told me to!

11:56.400 --> 11:59.631
l have tried to get rid of things,
but all this stuff is my life.

11:59.720 --> 12:01.631
Well, how old are you? 1 90?

12:01.720 --> 12:05.030
(Mimics his Ulster accent)
Get a grip, big man.

12:13.240 --> 12:15.151
Thank you.

12:15.240 --> 12:16.753
No milk?

12:16.840 --> 12:18.353
No fridge.

12:18.440 --> 12:20.351
Ah-ha. Fridge.

12:20.440 --> 12:23.716
- And the loo doesn't flush properly.
- Oh, l'm already onto that.

12:23.800 --> 12:25.153
You've fixed it?

12:25.240 --> 12:27.196
No, but l've made a note to.

12:33.440 --> 12:36.398
You know what l'm looking forward to most?

12:36.480 --> 12:38.391
What?

12:38.480 --> 12:40.516
Not having to be apart again.

12:42.520 --> 12:44.476
What about you?

12:44.560 --> 12:46.516
Having more space.

12:48.000 --> 12:49.911
l mean...

12:50.000 --> 12:51.956
look at all this crap.

12:53.280 --> 12:55.430
''The World's Greatest Lover.''

12:55.520 --> 12:58.353
Who gave you this? Your first boyfriend?

12:58.440 --> 13:01.352
- How did you know?
- lt's written in crayon.

13:01.440 --> 13:03.510
Do we really need to keep this?

13:03.600 --> 13:05.511
Sentimental value.

13:05.600 --> 13:08.717
l have very fond memories of that afternoon.

13:08.800 --> 13:10.756
Fake wedding certificate.

13:12.800 --> 13:16.270
- No, no, no, no. Let's have a look.
- Adam, give...

13:16.360 --> 13:17.839
''Rachel Louise Bradley,

13:17.920 --> 13:20.388
and Kris - with a K - Bumstead.

13:20.480 --> 13:21.993
Students.''

13:22.880 --> 13:25.519
Were they giving these out
in rag week or something?

13:25.600 --> 13:26.715
Sort of.

13:26.800 --> 13:28.711
lt's not very funny.

13:28.800 --> 13:30.870
No, it wasn't. That's why it didn't last.

13:33.160 --> 13:35.071
No-one knows...

13:35.160 --> 13:37.116
Well, except Kris.

13:39.840 --> 13:41.796
l once got married.

13:42.800 --> 13:44.472
What?

13:44.560 --> 13:46.596
l know. lt was a long time ago.

13:52.800 --> 13:54.711
This is real?

13:57.600 --> 13:59.511
We were young...

14:01.560 --> 14:04.233
You were married and you never told me?

14:05.320 --> 14:07.550
How could you not tell me, Rach?

14:07.640 --> 14:09.596
l forgot.

14:10.960 --> 14:12.871
l've been trying to forget.

14:12.960 --> 14:14.632
- How long did it last?
- 23 days.

14:14.720 --> 14:17.029
Then he'd slept with my best friend.

14:17.120 --> 14:18.473
- Bastard.
- l know.

14:18.560 --> 14:20.755
Not him, you!

14:20.840 --> 14:22.193
How could you not tell me?

14:22.280 --> 14:25.192
lt didn't seem to matter...
lt was less than a month.

14:25.280 --> 14:27.316
l've had plenty of boyfriends for longer.

14:27.400 --> 14:29.231
Boyfriends, yes. Husbands, no!

14:31.440 --> 14:33.396
Rach.

14:39.520 --> 14:41.476
When did you get divorced?

14:44.480 --> 14:46.755
That's the other thing l haven't told you.

14:53.640 --> 14:55.198
Bingo.

15:02.320 --> 15:04.276
Do you want to have sex?

15:04.360 --> 15:06.316
- You're joking?
- Yes.

15:08.160 --> 15:11.038
Four hours.
lf we're lucky, we might get four hours.

15:11.120 --> 15:13.076
So long as nothing disturbs him.

15:14.840 --> 15:16.796
(Knock at door)

15:16.880 --> 15:18.836
(Baby cries)

15:26.400 --> 15:28.356
Good. You're still up.

15:29.400 --> 15:30.435
Come in.

15:30.520 --> 15:31.475
Rachel?

15:31.560 --> 15:35.473
Sorry to come round so late.
l tried ringing, but you were engaged.

15:35.560 --> 15:37.391
l thought we were sleeping... Ramona.

15:37.480 --> 15:39.835
- What's happened?
- She must have the cordless.

15:39.920 --> 15:42.150
We've had a row. Adam's walked out.

15:42.240 --> 15:44.151
Ramona, get off the phone!

15:44.240 --> 15:46.151
Why would he just walk out?

15:46.240 --> 15:48.390
Because l told him l'm married.

15:48.480 --> 15:50.516
BOTH: Married?

15:50.600 --> 15:52.670
- Married?
- Yes, married.

15:52.760 --> 15:54.671
- Rachel's married.
- Married?

15:54.760 --> 15:56.671
Yes, married.

15:56.760 --> 15:58.034
ln name only.

15:58.120 --> 15:59.997
Bumstead?

16:00.080 --> 16:01.991
Well, l never used it.

16:02.080 --> 16:04.594
Well, you wouldn't, would you?

16:04.680 --> 16:08.832
Rachel, l've known you for six years.
You've never mentioned this.

16:08.920 --> 16:10.876
Believe me, l'd remember.

16:12.040 --> 16:13.951
Well, he broke my heart.

16:14.040 --> 16:15.996
Who wants to talk about it?

16:17.960 --> 16:20.269
l suppose l hoped it would just...

16:20.360 --> 16:22.271
go away.

16:22.360 --> 16:24.271
So...

16:24.360 --> 16:27.079
have you seen your husband since?

16:29.760 --> 16:33.355
He and Suzie went off to lndia together,
to live in an ashram.

16:34.400 --> 16:37.551
The last time l saw them was the day they left.

16:38.400 --> 16:41.312
Look, Adam will come round.

16:41.400 --> 16:44.631
l mean, you're not going to have
a problem getting a divorce!

16:45.680 --> 16:47.591
<i>ADAM: She doesn't want one.</i>

16:47.680 --> 16:49.591
- What?
- Why?

16:49.680 --> 16:51.716
Because l'm insisting on it.

16:55.480 --> 16:57.436
We had a row.

16:58.520 --> 17:00.476
A big row.

17:01.920 --> 17:03.831
She threw my gnome at me.

17:03.920 --> 17:05.830
You're lucky it's plastic.

17:05.920 --> 17:09.390
l feel so betrayed.
How could she not have told me?

17:09.480 --> 17:12.836
Adam, all couples
have secrets from each other.

17:12.920 --> 17:15.480
- We don't.
- Not that they're married to someone else!

17:15.560 --> 17:17.471
Do we?

17:17.560 --> 17:19.073
This changes everything.

17:19.160 --> 17:21.720
No, it doesn't. Rachel's no different.

17:21.800 --> 17:23.711
She has a husband!

17:23.800 --> 17:26.030
l'm living with a married woman!

17:26.119 --> 17:29.112
- My mother'll have a fit.
- Well, don't tell her!

17:29.200 --> 17:31.509
Yeah, it worked for Rachel long enough.

17:31.600 --> 17:34.433
l said to her,
''Listen, you bollocks, you better get a divorce.''

17:34.520 --> 17:37.796
- What was her reaction?
- The gnome.

17:38.600 --> 17:40.830
Then she yelled something about

17:40.920 --> 17:45.072
how she won't have me dictating
who she can and can't marry.

17:45.160 --> 17:47.071
Anyway, l was gone...

17:47.160 --> 17:49.754
Oh, yeah, that's another thing. Can l stay?

17:49.840 --> 17:52.559
(Both laugh uproariously, then stop)

18:05.640 --> 18:10.156
Well, l see your economy drive
hasn't reached your wine cellar.

18:10.240 --> 18:13.755
But l have made one significant saving -
l put a lock on the phone.

18:13.840 --> 18:15.796
He lets me have a key.

18:18.840 --> 18:20.751
Right, well,

18:20.840 --> 18:22.751
to business.

18:22.840 --> 18:26.549
The Lord giveth,
and the lnland Revenue taketh away.

18:26.640 --> 18:29.837
But sometimes they giveth back - a tax rebate.

18:29.920 --> 18:32.514
- ln fact, £1 ,000.
- A skiing holiday.

18:32.600 --> 18:35.194
A chance to recoup some of our losses.

18:35.280 --> 18:38.397
l see. Your harebrained scheme, our losses.

18:38.480 --> 18:41.677
- So what do you recommend, Larry?
- Marriage guidance. (Chuckles)

18:43.320 --> 18:46.869
lt really does depend on how much risk
you want to take.

18:46.960 --> 18:48.916
Probably less than you have.

18:49.000 --> 18:51.514
You still have time to take out a PEP,

18:51.600 --> 18:54.114
or a unit trust might be worth a look.

18:54.200 --> 18:56.191
- Do you have any literature?
- Reams.

18:57.280 --> 18:58.793
Right.

18:59.880 --> 19:03.668
We'll have a look through this lot
and make a decision.

19:03.760 --> 19:06.399
l don't think fiscal prudence is quite your forte.

19:06.480 --> 19:08.710
l'm not sure it's yours, old man.

19:08.800 --> 19:12.236
- lsn't your golf course waterlogged?
- And Marxist?

19:22.840 --> 19:26.674
<i>TV: Mia Farrow was once married to
which singer- Tony Bennett or Frank Sinatra?</i>

19:26.760 --> 19:28.716
Frank Sinatra. Frank Sinatra.

19:28.800 --> 19:30.711
<i>Frank Sinatra.</i>

19:30.800 --> 19:32.756
<i>(AppIause)</i>

19:35.120 --> 19:37.076
<i>It is so cIose.</i>

19:38.840 --> 19:43.675
Which French general said to his wife,
''Not tonight, Josephine''?

19:43.760 --> 19:46.718
(Baby cries)
- l missed that answer!

19:47.760 --> 19:50.479
At least we know he's not constipated.

19:50.560 --> 19:51.754
(Jenny growls)

19:51.840 --> 19:53.990
Please! l'm trying to eat here.

19:54.080 --> 19:55.991
(Crying continues)

19:56.080 --> 19:58.071
Doesn't he ever stop crying?

19:58.160 --> 20:00.958
- Only when he's asleep.
- Not very often, then.

20:01.040 --> 20:02.951
- Pete?
- Yeah?

20:03.040 --> 20:05.031
Where's my milk l expressed?

20:05.120 --> 20:07.076
lt's not in here.

20:08.640 --> 20:10.596
(Retches)

20:13.840 --> 20:15.796
Very funny.

20:18.160 --> 20:20.310
<i>KAREN: It's reaIIy IoveIy, RacheI.</i>

20:20.400 --> 20:22.311
Yeah, it's nice.

20:22.400 --> 20:24.755
Well, it could be nice.

20:26.400 --> 20:28.311
lt's lacking something.

20:28.400 --> 20:30.311
Furniture?

20:30.400 --> 20:32.356
Adam.

20:33.680 --> 20:35.432
Ah.

20:40.240 --> 20:42.196
(Silent exchange)

20:43.840 --> 20:45.751
How is Adam?

20:45.840 --> 20:48.479
Er, yeah, he's fine. You know, great.

20:49.240 --> 20:51.196
More trouble than the baby.

20:53.040 --> 20:55.554
Yesterday, he offered to baby-sit.

20:55.640 --> 20:57.471
Bye.

20:57.560 --> 20:59.471
Trust me.

20:59.560 --> 21:01.869
We went for a walk, not a long one.

21:01.960 --> 21:04.793
l didn't trust either of them to behave.

21:04.880 --> 21:10.637
Somebody told Adam that newborn babies
have a highly-developed survival instinct.

21:10.720 --> 21:14.838
<i>So you can get them to grip a rope,
and they'II know not to Iet go.</i>

21:26.720 --> 21:29.075
Thank God he landed in some washing.

21:29.160 --> 21:31.071
What, and Adam told you this?

21:31.160 --> 21:33.230
<i>The next-door neighbour did.</i>

21:36.640 --> 21:38.358
Rach, please get a divorce.

21:39.680 --> 21:41.238
Go on. Eh?

21:41.320 --> 21:43.231
For me.

21:43.320 --> 21:46.312
None of us like to be told what to do by our men,

21:46.400 --> 21:48.436
and usually it's grounds to do the opposite,

21:48.520 --> 21:51.910
but in this case,
and l say this as your closest friend,

21:52.000 --> 21:53.956
who thought she knew everything about you,

21:54.040 --> 21:58.989
l am 1 00%, completely,
totally and utterly in Adam's camp on this one.

21:59.080 --> 22:01.036
Me, too.

22:02.600 --> 22:05.990
Look, l am not being stubborn, it's just that...

22:08.560 --> 22:10.915
l am being stubborn, aren't l?

22:11.800 --> 22:13.438
Directory enquiries 1 92.

22:13.520 --> 22:15.238
What if he's ex-directory?

22:15.320 --> 22:17.276
As in ex-husband?

22:24.840 --> 22:27.400
Can l tell you something...man to man?

22:29.840 --> 22:31.751
l hate my life.

22:31.840 --> 22:36.072
l love the baby,
but it's everything else that goes with him.

22:36.160 --> 22:38.754
- Fatherhood.
- lt's hell.

22:38.840 --> 22:41.070
lt's no fun being a house guest either.

22:41.160 --> 22:44.789
l am a complete physical
and psychological wreck.

22:44.880 --> 22:48.589
ln Libya,
they use babies as instruments of torture,

22:48.680 --> 22:50.636
to extract confessions.

22:51.680 --> 22:54.558
- Does Jenny feel the same way?
- Oh, no way. She's a woman.

22:54.640 --> 22:56.756
- Comes naturally to her.
- Mm.

22:59.400 --> 23:02.358
Do you think she'll have dinner ready yet?

23:02.440 --> 23:04.715
We'd best give her five minutes.

23:06.760 --> 23:09.115
- Time for a pint, then.
- Pint, yeah.

23:09.640 --> 23:11.596
♪ Piano

23:18.640 --> 23:19.755
Hi.

23:19.840 --> 23:21.751
Oh, thanks.

23:46.920 --> 23:48.831
So what do we do here?

23:48.920 --> 23:51.912
Kiss, or are you going to take a swing at me?

24:01.600 --> 24:02.953
Hiya.

24:03.800 --> 24:05.711
Hi.

24:06.320 --> 24:08.629
<i>ADAM: She's meeting him for a drink?</i>

24:08.720 --> 24:11.393
- l thought you'd be pleased.
- That she's on a date with him?

24:11.480 --> 24:13.994
lt is not a date.
She just wants to discuss a divorce.

24:14.080 --> 24:17.709
What's to discuss? ''l want a divorce.''
She could put that on a postcard.

24:17.800 --> 24:21.429
And still have room
for ''lots of love'' on the bottom.

24:21.520 --> 24:24.034
lt happens to be over a glass of wine,

24:24.120 --> 24:26.793
but l'm telling you, Rachel was dreading it.

24:26.880 --> 24:31.874
lmagine how traumatic she'll find it -
dredging up painful memories.

24:35.480 --> 24:39.393
At least l didn't sound like
l was having an asthma attack.

24:39.480 --> 24:40.879
(Wheezing gasps)

24:40.960 --> 24:42.359
(Grunts)

24:42.440 --> 24:44.829
- l was having an asthma attack.
- No? Really?

24:44.920 --> 24:46.717
(Both laugh)

24:50.840 --> 24:53.718
- Well, at least l didn't weep.
- Oh, once!

24:53.800 --> 24:57.839
That happened once,
and no other woman's made me do that.

24:59.040 --> 25:00.996
Not even Suzie?

25:01.840 --> 25:03.796
Ouch.

25:05.240 --> 25:07.231
- How is she?
- Suzie?

25:07.320 --> 25:09.356
- Yeah.
- Dunno.

25:09.440 --> 25:11.351
We only lasted about a week.

25:11.440 --> 25:15.592
As soon as we got to lndia,
she dumped me for the yoga teacher.

25:15.680 --> 25:17.591
l think he was more supple.

25:17.680 --> 25:19.636
Wow, that is supple.

25:24.160 --> 25:26.037
You know, Suzie never meant anything to me.

25:28.320 --> 25:30.231
Well, more fool you, then.

25:30.320 --> 25:32.276
Yeah.

25:33.400 --> 25:35.311
<i>ADAM: No, no, no, no.</i>

25:35.400 --> 25:38.358
l'm not happy about this, not happy at all.

25:38.440 --> 25:41.034
Clearly too upset to do the drying-up.

25:41.120 --> 25:43.953
l tell you what. l'll take him out for a pint,
cheer him up.

25:44.040 --> 25:46.270
Leave me with the dishes? Sweet.

25:46.360 --> 25:48.874
You two go out. Don't worry about me.

25:48.960 --> 25:52.077
l'll stay here, baby-sit.

25:52.160 --> 25:54.071
BOTH: No!

25:54.160 --> 25:57.516
There you are.
He's woken up - too many blankets.

25:57.600 --> 26:00.558
- Any less, he'd catch a chill.
- Any more, he'd overheat.

26:00.640 --> 26:02.756
- Main cause of cot death.
- What?

26:02.840 --> 26:04.796
- l saw it on Casualty.
(Baby crying)

26:05.640 --> 26:07.551
Right, Pete.

26:07.640 --> 26:09.596
Can l have a word? Now!

26:11.440 --> 26:13.396
Well done.

26:22.960 --> 26:25.520
God, Rachel, it's so good to see you.

26:27.680 --> 26:29.477
lt was worth hitching up from London for.

26:29.560 --> 26:31.471
You hitched?

26:31.560 --> 26:34.120
Yeah. As soon as l got your message.

26:35.840 --> 26:39.992
lt's funny, innit? You run these things
over and over in your mind,

26:40.080 --> 26:42.355
and they never turn out that way in real life,

26:42.440 --> 26:44.431
but this one has.

26:47.080 --> 26:49.548
l always hoped we could be mates again.

26:52.840 --> 26:55.638
You know, we can meet up like this and...

27:00.640 --> 27:02.551
Anyway...

27:03.640 --> 27:06.029
You said you had something
to talk to me about.

27:07.240 --> 27:09.151
Oh.

27:09.240 --> 27:11.196
Yeah...

27:15.240 --> 27:17.196
Let's get some more wine.

27:18.240 --> 27:20.117
OK.

27:21.840 --> 27:25.196
What a catch. What a catch.

27:27.840 --> 27:30.798
- Get a bollocking, did you?
- Nah...

27:31.840 --> 27:33.592
Yeah.

27:34.640 --> 27:36.551
Look, Adam...

27:36.640 --> 27:38.551
Erm...

27:38.640 --> 27:42.952
Jenny and me.
l... We...think it's about time you moved on.

27:43.040 --> 27:46.237
You can't be comfortable sleeping on a couch.

27:46.320 --> 27:49.392
Don't worry about me. l can sleep anywhere.

27:50.040 --> 27:51.996
Er...no, you can't.

27:54.720 --> 27:56.631
Not here.

27:56.720 --> 28:00.190
We've been having a difficult time
with the baby.

28:00.280 --> 28:03.829
You'd be more than welcome back
when he's older...

28:03.920 --> 28:06.832
- 1 6 or so.
- Jenny wants me to leave?

28:07.880 --> 28:08.676
Tonight.

28:08.760 --> 28:11.558
Tonight? l've got to go and pack my bag now?

28:12.720 --> 28:16.235
She's already packed it for you.
lt's by the door.

28:22.440 --> 28:25.238
♪ Put your sweet lips...
- This is a great week.

28:25.320 --> 28:30.599
♪ ..up closer to the phone

28:31.640 --> 28:39.832
♪ Let's pretend that we're together all alone

28:39.920 --> 28:49.158
♪ l'll tell the man
to turn the jukebox way down low

28:49.240 --> 28:52.357
♪ And you tell your friend...

28:52.440 --> 28:54.351
Yeah? Can l help you?

28:54.440 --> 28:57.512
♪ You'll have to...

28:57.600 --> 29:00.956
Rachel's boyfriend? Kris.

29:01.040 --> 29:02.359
Rachel's husband?

29:02.440 --> 29:04.351
Yeah. Look, come in, mate.

29:04.440 --> 29:06.396
Make yourself at home.

29:09.560 --> 29:11.471
Sorry, l'm a bit...

29:11.560 --> 29:13.471
l didn't expect you to be...

29:13.560 --> 29:14.629
Black?

29:14.720 --> 29:16.199
Here.

29:17.400 --> 29:18.958
Where's Rachel?

29:19.040 --> 29:21.793
(Toilet flushes)
- She erm... She had a bit too much to drink.

29:21.880 --> 29:24.633
- Threw up all over my top.
- You were standing that close?

29:24.720 --> 29:26.676
lt was projectile.

29:26.760 --> 29:28.716
Adam!

29:29.840 --> 29:31.592
l-l wasn't expecting you home.

29:31.680 --> 29:33.591
So it would seem.

29:33.680 --> 29:36.638
- Really glad you're back.
- Why? ls the loo still buggered?

29:37.000 --> 29:38.911
Yeah, a little bit, but...

29:39.000 --> 29:40.319
l've missed you.

29:40.400 --> 29:42.311
Really?

29:42.400 --> 29:46.234
l'll go and put some coffee on.
Strong and black, yeah?

29:51.840 --> 29:53.193
Excellent.

29:53.280 --> 29:55.191
Since 1 st July, 1 994,

29:55.280 --> 30:01.355
UK companies may pay dividends
as foreign income dividends.

30:01.440 --> 30:02.998
What does that mean?

30:03.080 --> 30:05.389
lt means you don't understand
what you're reading.

30:05.480 --> 30:09.473
Who can blame me? l've just read a sentence
five lines long with only one verb in it.

30:09.560 --> 30:12.279
- Who writes stuff like that?
- Lawyers.

30:12.360 --> 30:15.909
Well, they should have it checked
by human beings.

30:16.000 --> 30:18.434
