35:50.760 --> 35:55.470
Just as l'm sure you didn't mean to imply
l love the baby any less than you do.

36:01.240 --> 36:03.196
Jen, what's happened to us?

36:08.440 --> 36:13.116
l thought babies brought couples together,
not drove them apart.

36:13.200 --> 36:16.670
Pete, it's so hard being a mum.

36:17.720 --> 36:20.029
l know it is, but you're good at it.

36:20.120 --> 36:21.838
No, l'm not.

36:21.920 --> 36:23.638
l'm a failure.

36:23.720 --> 36:26.757
No, l'm a failure, as a husband and a father.

36:27.640 --> 36:30.757
(Baby cries)
- Oh, God.

36:30.840 --> 36:33.798
No, wait. Just let him cry for a little bit.

36:33.880 --> 36:38.158
Look, we're talking, aren't we?
That's progress, isn't it?

36:42.240 --> 36:45.789
We can't be the first parents to find it difficult.

36:45.880 --> 36:49.190
Everyone else seemed to cope,
even my parents.

36:49.280 --> 36:51.236
(Baby continues crying)

36:52.440 --> 36:54.351
Oh, God, Pete.

36:54.440 --> 36:56.351
l love you so much.

36:56.440 --> 37:01.036
And l love our baby. l just wish
sometimes that he would just stop...

37:01.120 --> 37:03.076
(Crying stops)

37:06.440 --> 37:08.396
Successful parenting.

37:11.800 --> 37:13.756
(Jenny sighs with relief)

37:18.440 --> 37:20.396
l might just check on him.

37:21.440 --> 37:23.396
Yeah.

37:24.240 --> 37:27.118
Kris thinks he might stay in Manchester.

37:27.280 --> 37:31.717
There's more chance of him breaking
into the music scene here.

37:31.800 --> 37:35.076
Rachel, you got in touch with Kris
to get a divorce.

37:35.160 --> 37:37.390
Now he's practically your lodger!

37:37.480 --> 37:39.436
We wouldn't charge him rent.

37:42.800 --> 37:44.711
Look, it's just temporary.

37:44.800 --> 37:46.711
And besides, he's...

37:46.800 --> 37:49.519
<i>he's reaIIy heIpfuI around the house.</i>

37:50.240 --> 37:52.151
(Flushes)

37:52.240 --> 37:54.390
- There you go.
- Adam'll be pleased.

37:54.480 --> 37:55.833
<i>KAREN: And was he?</i>

37:55.920 --> 37:57.239
Ooh. Hang on.

37:57.320 --> 37:58.639
<i>He didn't seem to be.</i>

37:58.720 --> 38:01.917
- Do you think you're being fair to him?
- To Adam?

38:02.000 --> 38:05.390
- l've let him move back into the bedroom.
- Great.

38:06.040 --> 38:07.951
He...gets on with Kris.

38:08.040 --> 38:09.473
They're almost friends.

38:09.560 --> 38:11.710
<i>They pIay chess together.</i>

38:13.760 --> 38:16.672
Yes! Yes! Yes!

38:16.760 --> 38:19.115
Do you remember that old chestnut -
two's company?

38:19.200 --> 38:22.112
- Mrs Marsden...
- Thanks.

38:22.200 --> 38:24.111
lt's not like that.

38:24.200 --> 38:26.111
Really?

38:28.200 --> 38:30.111
PETE: Left foot blue!
- (Contorted cries)

38:30.200 --> 38:32.111
Kris is the winner!

38:32.200 --> 38:35.033
- Again?
- Hey, come on. Another game.

38:36.600 --> 38:38.716
ADAM: l'll get us some more drinks.

38:39.760 --> 38:42.718
KRlS: Do you want another go?
- Yeah.

38:45.400 --> 38:46.753
KRlS: Spin.

38:46.840 --> 38:48.751
He seems like a top bloke.

38:48.840 --> 38:50.751
He's a wanker.

38:50.840 --> 38:52.751
He's certainly supple.

38:52.840 --> 38:56.628
Yeah. Exactly.
Did you notice it was him suggested Twister?

38:56.720 --> 38:59.518
Adam, nobody else wanted to play chess.

39:00.560 --> 39:02.471
Right hand green.

39:02.560 --> 39:06.473
- (Laughs) Oh, no way!
KRlS: No, you've got to.

39:06.560 --> 39:08.232
Hey! What are you at?

39:08.320 --> 39:10.880
- Look, you're pressing down on me.
- You're pressing up.

39:10.960 --> 39:13.554
Rach, your arse touched. You're out.

39:13.640 --> 39:14.755
That is not true!

39:14.840 --> 39:17.957
Yeah, both cheeks, didn't they, Pete?
Come on. Pack it in.

39:18.040 --> 39:20.759
KRlS: Oh, the undisputed champion.

39:20.840 --> 39:22.796
Yeah, l'll take you up.

39:24.680 --> 39:26.159
- Are you in, Pete?
- No.

39:26.240 --> 39:28.959
Oh, no. Just the two of us. One on one.

39:29.800 --> 39:31.756
Mano e mano.

39:34.480 --> 39:37.074
Rach, l think you should come back in.

39:37.160 --> 39:39.071
Why? ls someone hurt?

39:39.160 --> 39:41.071
No, not yet.

39:41.160 --> 39:43.116
Hey, left foot green, Adam.

39:46.920 --> 39:49.115
(Kris chokes)

39:58.360 --> 40:00.510
l think it's time we were going.

40:00.600 --> 40:02.511
Yeah.

40:02.600 --> 40:04.556
Not the only ones.

40:11.000 --> 40:13.230
You put it in a building society?

40:13.320 --> 40:15.595
What's wrong with that? At least there's no risk.

40:15.680 --> 40:16.829
No interest.

40:18.440 --> 40:23.275
So, which esteemed investment house
did you entrust with our wealth?

40:23.360 --> 40:25.669
l don't know. lt had a blue carpet.

40:25.760 --> 40:28.593
- That must have swung it for you.
- l did shop around.

40:28.680 --> 40:31.035
Well, that we know you're good at.

40:31.840 --> 40:34.673
Did you go to the family planning clinic?

40:34.760 --> 40:37.069
No. Still haven't made up my mind.

40:37.160 --> 40:41.119
We cannot afford another child right now.
l thought we'd agreed.

40:41.200 --> 40:43.156
We agreed to think about it.

40:44.600 --> 40:46.511
Yeah.

40:46.600 --> 40:48.750
Let's think about it tomorrow.

40:48.840 --> 40:52.116
But, darling, l thought you didn't want
any costly mistakes.

40:52.200 --> 40:54.111
Oh, don't worry.

40:54.200 --> 40:58.193
Before l leave a deposit,
l can make a timely withdrawal.

40:58.280 --> 41:01.670
But, darling,
you pinpointed the problem yourself...

41:02.720 --> 41:04.676
No interest.

41:20.160 --> 41:22.071
Kris.

41:22.160 --> 41:26.119
(Football commentator on TV)
- Can l have a word, while Adam's out?

41:26.200 --> 41:27.679
(Volume lowered)

41:29.840 --> 41:32.035
You know how much
l've enjoyed having you here.

41:33.560 --> 41:35.516
Yeah, l know you know.

41:37.520 --> 41:39.431
But...

41:39.520 --> 41:41.476
we can't go on like this.

41:43.040 --> 41:44.951
Or at all.

41:46.040 --> 41:49.077
Look, the thing is,
l'm really glad we're friends and...

41:51.720 --> 41:53.631
..l loved you once, but...

41:53.720 --> 41:55.631
l love Adam now.

41:55.720 --> 41:58.951
My future's with him.
And l don't want to jeopardise that.

42:02.840 --> 42:07.072
l never told you the real reason
l got in touch with you again.

42:07.160 --> 42:09.116
Oh, this isn't easy.

42:11.000 --> 42:12.956
You want a divorce.

42:15.760 --> 42:17.716
lt's all right. No problem.

42:20.840 --> 42:22.796
That was easy.

42:25.320 --> 42:28.073
Oh, the other thing is, you've got to move out.

42:28.160 --> 42:32.073
l know you've got nowhere else to go
and that you're broke...

42:32.160 --> 42:34.116
l want to help you with that.

42:36.160 --> 42:38.116
Oh, Rach...

42:39.200 --> 42:40.758
l couldn't.

42:40.840 --> 42:45.391
lt's not a loan. l'm paying you off.
Take it and go back to London.

42:47.960 --> 42:51.953
- Don't say you haven't got a price.
- lt's not that. lt's just that Rachel...

42:52.040 --> 42:54.076
Look, l don't want to hear it.

42:56.520 --> 42:58.476
OK, then.

43:01.640 --> 43:03.596
Bumstead only has one M.

43:05.640 --> 43:07.596
Oh, sorry.

43:09.200 --> 43:11.111
One other thing.

43:11.200 --> 43:13.270
Rach isn't to know about this,

43:13.360 --> 43:15.271
not ever.

43:15.360 --> 43:17.999
You want this to be just our little secret?

43:18.160 --> 43:19.912
Please.

43:21.680 --> 43:24.513
l wish you wouldn't do this.

43:24.600 --> 43:26.556
l want to.

43:27.280 --> 43:29.191
OK, then.

43:29.960 --> 43:31.518
Thanks.

43:31.600 --> 43:33.192
You're welcome.

43:36.120 --> 43:38.111
Wasn't that game on earlier?

43:38.200 --> 43:40.111
Yeah.

43:40.200 --> 43:42.156
These are the highlights.

43:50.800 --> 43:52.711
Well, bye, then, mate.

43:52.800 --> 43:54.552
Bye.

43:56.800 --> 43:58.756
l'll see you.

44:01.920 --> 44:03.876
(Engine starts)

44:09.840 --> 44:11.796
Missing you already.

44:21.040 --> 44:22.996
(Phone rings)

44:31.280 --> 44:33.236
(Continues ringing)

44:34.840 --> 44:36.751
Hello?

44:36.840 --> 44:38.353
No, l will not accept the charges!

44:38.440 --> 44:40.590
David! Ramona's mother's ill.

44:40.680 --> 44:42.591
She could be dying.

44:42.680 --> 44:44.591
OK. Put them through.

44:44.680 --> 44:46.591
Ramona!

44:46.680 --> 44:48.079
Telephone!

44:48.160 --> 44:49.673
Surprise, surprise.

44:49.760 --> 44:51.193
Ramona!

44:51.280 --> 44:52.998
Telephone!

44:56.520 --> 44:58.556
Erm, uno momento, por favor.

45:00.920 --> 45:03.354
lf you're looking for your investments,

45:03.440 --> 45:06.318
they're at the bottom of a very long list.

45:08.360 --> 45:11.318
By the way, is your interest paid monthly,

45:11.400 --> 45:13.356
cos l need to buy a stamp.

45:14.280 --> 45:16.714
Don't worry, second class will do.

45:16.800 --> 45:18.711
Qué hay!

45:18.800 --> 45:21.712
No te he visto en demasiado tiempo!

45:21.800 --> 45:23.756
Yo también, my darling!

45:26.440 --> 45:29.273
l don't think her mother could have died.

45:29.360 --> 45:31.271
No. Ramona!

45:31.360 --> 45:33.316
Ramona!

45:48.440 --> 45:50.396
That was fun.

45:52.440 --> 45:54.908
l didn't handle it very well, did l?

45:56.960 --> 45:58.916
No.

46:01.960 --> 46:03.916
Would sorry help at all?

46:05.960 --> 46:07.871
lt might.

46:07.960 --> 46:09.916
Try it.

46:11.760 --> 46:13.716
Adam, l'm sorry.

46:17.240 --> 46:19.196
Come here.

46:36.440 --> 46:38.396
Shall we move in together?

46:40.440 --> 46:42.396
Our house.

46:44.040 --> 46:45.996
ln the middle of our street.

46:52.440 --> 46:55.398
l bet you thought we'd never get rid of him.

46:55.480 --> 46:59.075
- Oh, l thought he might be going today.
- Oh, you did, did you?

46:59.160 --> 47:01.993
He had 500 bloody good reasons for going.

47:02.080 --> 47:05.231
- So he told you?
- What?

47:05.320 --> 47:07.231
About our arrangement.

47:07.320 --> 47:09.231
What arrangement?

47:09.320 --> 47:11.356
- £500.
- That was our arrangement.

47:11.440 --> 47:13.351
- Who?
- What?

47:13.440 --> 47:16.352
l gave Kris £500 to go away.

47:16.440 --> 47:18.396
So did l.

47:22.040 --> 47:23.996
Excellent.

47:25.440 --> 47:28.398
There goes one thousand pounds.

47:29.440 --> 47:31.396
There goes our sofa.

47:34.960 --> 47:36.871
This must have set you back a bit.

47:36.960 --> 47:39.110
l thought after the Kris business you were broke.

47:39.200 --> 47:41.111
We are.

47:41.200 --> 47:43.873
Yeah, but some really good friends
lent us the money.

47:43.960 --> 47:45.313
(Whispers) Shut up.

47:45.400 --> 47:48.119
l must tell you a story about Karen and money -

47:48.200 --> 47:51.351
how to make a million pounds in as many years.

47:53.400 --> 47:58.076
Well, Karen decided to take a greater interest
in our finances - doesn't matter why.

47:58.160 --> 48:00.310
Oh, this is jolly comfortable.

48:00.400 --> 48:03.233
- Anyway...
- Oh, shut up, David.

